content.body: This is not just any hotel lobby bar. There’s nothing better than nestling yourself into one of the plush velvet or leather armchairs, martini in hand, and gazing up at that incredible nine-floor atrium. And Tom Colicchio’s classic small bites never disappoint.
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body:
Where locals & visitors alike can experience a version of old New York centered around Tom Colicchio's signature cooking style & the inventive handcrafted cocktails created by our resident bar team. 

Located beneath a stunning, nine-story Victorian era atrium, The Bar Room is set with rich, jewel-toned furnishings delivering stylish ambiance for celebratory libations and indelible dining. Our menus are the perfect match for our collection of classic and modern cocktail creations. Timeless culinary favorites include locally sourced Oysters on the Half Shell, Caramelized Onion Dip & Tom Colicchio's Signature Wagyu Burger. Classics like our Brioche French Toast join the weekend lineup at brunch, and our indulgent desserts from Executive Pastry Chef, Abby Swain are available nightly. The Bar Room at The Beekman is open all day serving breakfast, dinner, lunch & weekend jazz brunch. Reservations are requested for all visits.

need_to_know.body:
Jazz Brunch is served every weekend featuring the Temple Court Quartet on Saturdays and The Jazz Bazaar on Sundays.

We have a 10 minute grace period. Please call us if you are running later than 10 minutes after your reservation time.

about.body:
Resting at the foot of a soaring, nine-story, glass atrium - is The Bar Room at The Beekman. Where our Tom Colicchio 'What's Local Is Best' culinary style and 'Make People Happy' brand of hospitality set us apart from the other dining destinations in Manhattan’s bustling Financial District. 

Now open for weekend breakfast & dinner, we invite you back to The Bar Room to explore our bar snack-inspired dinner menu, raise a glass from our fully restored handcrafted cocktail menu & expertly curated wine list or celebrate the seasons during weekend brunch or breakfast. Our spectacular surroundings still delivering a distinctly old New York feel, now updated to prioritize the health and safety of our guests.

need_to_know.body:
Please call us if you are running later than our 10 minute grace period.  Parties of 1-2 may keep their table for 1.5 hours, parties of 3-4 for 2 hours, parties of 5+ for 2.5 hours. Our last reservation is 1045pm, kitchen closes at 11pm, guests are welcome to join us on a walk in basis until last call at 12am.


For further inquiries, please contact reservations@templecourtnyc.com or 212.658.1848.

**Important Dining Information**
Parties of 9+ have a $50 per person, per hour minimum spend. Gratuity and tax are additional. No-Shows/Cancelation within 24 hours results in $50 per person fee.

We have a 10 minute grace period. Please call us if you are running later than 10 minutes after your reservation time.  Parties of 1-2 may keep their table for 1.5 hours, parties of 3-4 for 2 hours, parties of 5+ for 2.5 hours. The last seating is 1030pm and the restaurant closes at 1130pm sharp. 

For further inquiries, please contact reservations@templecourtnyc.com or 212.658.1848.

content.body: This is tweezer food we actually want to eat. Artesano goes about Peruvian cuisine with a precision we don’t see often: Think octopus emulsions, rocoto gel, and cauliflower tiger’s milk alongside more robust dishes like Peruvian fried rice and short ribs.
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body:
Artesano, a new Peruvian restaurant in Tribeca, is aiming to give diners a taste of South America without the hours-long flight.

Artesano's philosophy is some of the best Sensory Experiences Happen on the Peruvian Plate. Taste the sentiments and nostalgia from a fusion of continents. Peruvian gastronomy, its influence & inclusiveness has opened the door for the marriages of many cultures & thus have ingrained themselves into the Peruvian gastronomic experience.
As long as the world continues to evolve, so will the kitchen. The end of possibilities is nowhere in sight.

need_to_know.body:
Our menu includes an A La Carte & Tasting Menu. Walk-ins are always accepted on a first-come-first-serve basis. All items on the tasting menu are available for A La Carte ordering. 
Parties of 8 or will be exclusively limited to our Prix Fixe or Tasting Menus.
As courtesy we hold your reservation for 15 minutes maximum.
